How does a try statement determine which catch clause should be used to handle an exception?

try kaise decide karta hai kaunsa catch chalega?

1Ô∏è‚É£ Error aate hi Java catch blocks ko upar se niche check karta hai

2Ô∏è‚É£ Jo catch error ke type se match karta hai,
wahi pehle wala catch execute hota hai

3Ô∏è‚É£ Agar exact match mil gaya ‚Üí wahi catch chalega
Agar exact nahi mila ‚Üí parent (bada) exception wala catch chalega
try {
    int a = 10 / 0;
}
catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.println("Math error");
}
catch (Exception e) {
    System.out.println("General error");
}

‚ùå Invalid:

catch (Exception e) { }
catch (ArithmeticException e) { } // Compile-time error
