Can a double value be cast to a byte?
Yes üëç double value ko byte me cast kiya ja sakta hai, lekin manually (explicit cast) karna padta hai.
Simple answer
double d = 130.7;
byte b = (byte) d;
System.out.println(b); // -126

Ye aisa kyon hota hai? (simple language)
1Ô∏è‚É£ double ‚Üí byte = narrowing conversion
üëâ Java automatically allow nahi karta
üëâ Isliye (byte) likhna compulsory hai
2Ô∏è‚É£ Decimal part cut ho jata hai
130.7 ‚Üí 130
3Ô∏è‚É£ Byte range hota hai:
-128 to 127
-128 to 127   (total 256 values)
2ka power 8 bits 8 bits ka hota hai 
4Ô∏è‚É£ Range se bahar value wrap ho jati hai
130 - 256 = -126
Aur examples
(double) 10.9  ‚Üí byte = 10
(double) 127.0 ‚Üí byte = 127
(double) 128.0 ‚Üí byte = -128
(double) -130  ‚Üí byte = 126

What is constructor chaining and how is it achieved in Java?
Constructor chaining is the process of calling one constructor from another constructor 
using this() for same class and super() for parent class to reuse code and ensure proper initialization.
1Ô∏è‚É£ this() aur super() ek hi constructor me saath me nahi ho sakte
2Ô∏è‚É£ Dono me se koi bhi ho ‚Üí first statement hona chahiye
3Ô∏è‚É£ Constructor chaining se initialization flow clear hota hai


super() ‚Äì parent class ke constructor ko call karne ke liye
class Parent {
    Parent() {
        System.out.println("Parent constructor");
    }
}

class Child extends Parent {
    Child() {
        super();   // parent constructor call
        System.out.println("Child constructor");
    }
}


Output:

Parent constructor
Child constructor
Agar super() likho ya na likho, Java automatically parent ka default constructor call karta hai.
---
1Ô∏è‚É£ this() ‚Äì same class ke constructor ko call karne ke liye
class Student {
    int id;
    String name;

    Student() {
        this(101, "Soni");   // same class ka constructor call
        System.out.println("Default constructor");
    }

    Student(int id, String name) {
        this.id = id;
        this.name = name;
        System.out.println("Parameterized constructor");
    }
}


Output:

Parameterized constructor
Default constructor


üîë Rule:

this() hamesha first line me likhna hota hai

